name: $registered
desc: This is a partial (e.g. initial, interim or preliminary) report: data in the report may be incomplete or unverified.

name: $partial
desc: The report is complete and verified by an authorized person.

name: $final
desc: Subsequent to being final, the report has been modified.  This includes any change in the results, diagnosis, narrative text, or other content of a report that has been issued.

name: $amended
desc: The report is unavailable because the measurement was not started or not completed (also sometimes called "aborted").

name: $cancelled
desc: The report has been withdrawn following a previous final release.  This electronic record should never have existed, though it is possible that real-world decisions were based on it. (If real-world activity has occurred, the status should be "cancelled" rather than "entered-in-error".).

name: $entered-in-error
desc: The authoring/source system does not know which of the status values currently applies for this observation. Note: This concept is not to be used for "other" - one of the listed statuses is presumed to apply, but the authoring/source system does not know which.
